Load the data

ca_county_cases <- 
  read_csv("https://raw.githubusercontent.com/datadesk/california-coronavirus-data/master/latimes-county-totals.csv")

bay_county_names <-
  c(
    "Alameda",
    "Contra Costa",
    "Marin",
    "Napa",
    "San Francisco",
    "San Mateo",
    "Santa Clara",
    "Solano",
    "Sonoma"
  )

bay_county_cases <-
  ca_county_cases %>% 
  filter(county %in% bay_county_names) %>% 
  filter(!is.na(confirmed_cases))


# social distancing data
bay_sd <- readRDS("/Users/simonespeizer/pCloud Drive/Shared/SFBI/Restricted Data Library/Safegraph/covid19analysis/bay_socialdistancing_v2.rds") %>% 
  mutate(date = date_range_start %>%  substr(1,10) %>% as.Date())

# obtaining weekends
weekends <- bay_sd %>% 
  filter(!duplicated(date)) %>% 
  arrange(date) %>% 
  mutate(weekend = ifelse((date %>% as.numeric()) %% 7 %in% c(2,3), T, F)) %>% 
  dplyr::select(date,weekend)

bay_sd <- bay_sd %>% left_join(weekends)

Initial analysis - Bay Area social distancing and case growth rate

The plot below demonstrates the case growth rate and the percent of devices leaving home relative to the average for January and February, up through right before the first date listed in the plot.

minCases <- 20

bay_county_cases_daily <- bay_county_cases %>%
  group_by(date) %>%
  summarize(total_cases_by_day = sum(confirmed_cases)) %>%
  filter(total_cases_by_day >= minCases) # only look at after cases have started to grow more substantially

# get cases shifted by a day to calculate growth rate
past_day_cases <- c(NA, bay_county_cases_daily$total_cases_by_day[1:(nrow(bay_county_cases_daily)-1)])

# calculate growth rate
bay_county_cases_daily <- bay_county_cases_daily %>% 
  cbind(past_day_cases) %>% 
  mutate(growth_rate = ((total_cases_by_day / past_day_cases) - 1)*100) 

# calculate the percent of devices leaving home on each date 
bay_sd_daily <- bay_sd %>%
  filter(date >= min(bay_county_cases_daily$date)) %>%
  group_by(date) %>%
  summarize(total_at_home = sum(completely_home_device_count), total_devices = sum(device_count)) %>%
  mutate(percent_at_home = total_at_home*100/total_devices, percent_leaving_home = (100 - percent_at_home))

# calculate the average percent of devices leaving home for all dates prior to the first day of case growth that we are considering here
pre_case_growth_at_home <- bay_sd %>%
  filter(date < min(bay_county_cases_daily$date)) %>%
  summarize(total_at_home = sum(completely_home_device_count), total_devices = sum(device_count)) %>%
  mutate(percent_at_home = total_at_home*100/total_devices, percent_leaving_home = (100 - percent_at_home))

# calculate the difference between each day's % leaving home and the average % leaving home before, and join with the case growth rate data
bay_sd_daily <- bay_sd_daily %>%
  mutate(leaving_home_dif = percent_leaving_home - pre_case_growth_at_home$percent_leaving_home[1]) %>%
  left_join(bay_county_cases_daily)

# plot
bay_sd_daily %>% ggplot(
  aes(x = date)) +
    geom_line(aes(y = leaving_home_dif, color="Leaving home")) +
  geom_line(aes(y = growth_rate-30, color = "Cases")) + 
  scale_y_continuous(sec.axis = sec_axis(~.*1+30, name = "Daily case growth rate (%)")) + 
  scale_colour_manual(values = c("red", "blue")) +
  labs(y = "Change in percent of devices leaving home relative to before", x = "Date", color = "Data", title = "LA Times Case Data and Social Distancing")

# try plotting with an adjusted date on the social distancing, pushing it back by 6 days
bay_sd_6_days_ago <- c(NA, NA, NA, NA, NA, NA, bay_sd_daily$leaving_home_dif[1:(nrow(bay_sd_daily)-6)])

bay_sd_daily_6_days <- bay_sd_daily %>% 
  cbind(bay_sd_6_days_ago)

bay_sd_daily_6_days %>% ggplot(
  aes(x = date)) +
    geom_line(aes(y = bay_sd_6_days_ago, color="Leaving home")) +
  geom_line(aes(y = growth_rate-30, color = "Cases")) + 
  scale_y_continuous(sec.axis = sec_axis(~.*1+30, name = "Daily case growth rate (%)")) + 
  scale_colour_manual(values = c("red", "blue")) +
  labs(y = "Change in percent of devices leaving home 6 days ago relative to before", x = "Date", color = "Data", title = "LA Times Case Data and Social Distancing, 6 Day Lag")

# also try with 7 day lag
bay_sd_7_days_ago <- c(NA, NA, NA, NA, NA, NA, NA, bay_sd_daily$leaving_home_dif[1:(nrow(bay_sd_daily)-7)])

bay_sd_daily_7_days <- bay_sd_daily %>% 
  cbind(bay_sd_7_days_ago)

bay_sd_daily_7_days %>% ggplot(
  aes(x = date)) +
    geom_line(aes(y = bay_sd_7_days_ago, color="Leaving home")) +
  geom_line(aes(y = growth_rate-30, color = "Cases")) + 
  scale_y_continuous(sec.axis = sec_axis(~.*1+30, name = "Daily case growth rate (%)")) + 
  scale_colour_manual(values = c("red", "blue")) +
  labs(y = "Change in percent of devices leaving home 7 days ago relative to before", x = "Date", color = "Data", title = "LA Times Case Data and Social Distancing, 7 Day Lag")

grangertest(bay_sd_daily$leaving_home_dif, bay_sd_daily$growth_rate, na.action = na.omit, order=7)
## Granger causality test
## 
## Model 1: bay_sd_daily$growth_rate ~ Lags(bay_sd_daily$growth_rate, 1:7) + Lags(bay_sd_daily$leaving_home_dif, 1:7)
## Model 2: bay_sd_daily$growth_rate ~ Lags(bay_sd_daily$growth_rate, 1:7)

## 1     45

Compare to NYT case data

county_cases_nyt <- 
  read_csv("https://raw.githubusercontent.com/nytimes/covid-19-data/master/us-counties.csv")

covid_nyt_bay_daily <- county_cases_nyt %>% 
  filter(state == "California") %>% 
  filter(county %in% bay_county_names) %>% 
  group_by(date) %>% 
  summarize(total_cases_by_day = sum(cases)) %>%
  filter(total_cases_by_day >= minCases) # again minimum number of cases to use

past_day_cases_nyt <- c(NA, covid_nyt_bay_daily$total_cases_by_day[1:nrow(covid_nyt_bay_daily)-1])

covid_nyt_bay_daily <- covid_nyt_bay_daily %>% 
  cbind(past_day_cases_nyt) %>% 
  mutate(growth_rate = ((total_cases_by_day / past_day_cases_nyt) - 1)*100)

bay_sd_daily_nyt_match <- bay_sd %>%
  filter(date >= min(covid_nyt_bay_daily$date)) %>%
  group_by(date) %>%
  summarize(total_at_home = sum(completely_home_device_count), total_devices = sum(device_count)) %>%
  mutate(percent_at_home = total_at_home*100/total_devices, percent_leaving_home = (100 - percent_at_home))

pre_case_growth_at_home_nyt <- bay_sd %>%
  filter(date < min(covid_nyt_bay_daily$date)) %>%
  summarize(total_at_home = sum(completely_home_device_count), total_devices = sum(device_count)) %>%
  mutate(percent_at_home = total_at_home*100/total_devices, percent_leaving_home = (100 - percent_at_home))


bay_sd_daily_nyt_match <- bay_sd_daily_nyt_match %>%
  mutate(leaving_home_dif = percent_leaving_home - pre_case_growth_at_home_nyt$percent_leaving_home[1]) %>%
  left_join(covid_nyt_bay_daily)

Trying things

Considering just the data from Santa Clara County and San Mateo County separately to see if this clarifies anything. Using methods from Derek applied to individual counties.

Santa Clara: (using just SJ social distancing data)

# get the SCC data on cases and SJ data on social distancing
sj_blockgroups <- readRDS("/Users/simonespeizer/Documents/2020 Spring Quarter/CEE 218Z/covid19/sj_blockgroups.rds")

scc_cases_sd_daily <- bay_sd %>% 
  filter(date >= min(bay_county_cases_daily$date)) %>%
  filter(origin_census_block_group %in% sj_blockgroups$origin_census_block_group) %>% 
  group_by(date) %>%
  summarize(total_at_home = sum(completely_home_device_count), total_devices = sum(device_count)) %>%
  mutate(
    percent_at_home = total_at_home*100/total_devices, 
    percent_leaving_home = (100 - percent_at_home)
  ) %>%
  left_join(
    bay_county_cases %>%
    filter(county == "Santa Clara") %>% 
    group_by(date) %>%
    summarize(total_cases_by_day = sum(confirmed_cases)) 
  ) %>% 
  mutate(
    log_cases = log(total_cases_by_day)
  ) 

# get the baseline percent of people at home
pre_case_growth_at_home <- bay_sd %>%
  filter(date < min(bay_county_cases_daily$date)) %>%
  filter(origin_census_block_group %in% sj_blockgroups$origin_census_block_group) %>%
  summarize(total_at_home = sum(completely_home_device_count), total_devices = sum(device_count)) %>%
  mutate(percent_at_home = total_at_home*100/total_devices, percent_leaving_home = (100 - percent_at_home))

# obtain difference in percent of people at home
scc_cases_sd_daily <- scc_cases_sd_daily %>%
  mutate(leaving_home_dif = percent_leaving_home - pre_case_growth_at_home$percent_leaving_home[1])

ndiffs(scc_cases_sd_daily$total_cases_by_day)
## [1] 2
ndiffs(scc_cases_sd_daily$log_cases[-1])
## [1] 2
ndiffs(scc_cases_sd_daily$percent_leaving_home)

scc_test <-
  scc_cases_sd_daily %>% 
  mutate(
    leaving_home_dif_mov_avg = movavg(leaving_home_dif, 7, type = "s"),
    dlog_cases = c(NA,diff(log_cases)),
    d2log_cases = c(NA,NA,diff(log_cases, differences = 2)),
    dcases = c(NA,diff(total_cases_by_day)),
    d2cases = c(NA,NA,diff(dcases, differences = 2)),
    dleaving = c(NA,diff(percent_leaving_home)),
    d2leaving = c(NA,NA,diff(percent_leaving_home, differences = 2)),
    cases_mov = movavg(total_cases_by_day, 7, type = "s"),
    log_cases_mov = movavg(log_cases, 7, type = "s"),
    log_cases_mov_4 = movavg(log_cases, 4, type = "s"),
    dlog_cases_mov = c(NA,diff(log_cases_mov)),
    dlog_cases_mov_4 = c(NA,diff(log_cases_mov_4)),
    d2log_cases_mov = c(NA,NA,diff(log_cases_mov, differences = 2)),
    d2log_cases_mov_4 = c(NA,NA,diff(log_cases_mov_4, differences = 2)),
    # dcases_mov = movavg(dcases, 7),
    # d2cases_mov = movavg(d2cases, 7),
    dcases_mov = c(NA,diff(cases_mov)),
    dcases_mov_4 = c(NA,diff(cases_mov)),
    d2cases_mov = c(NA,diff(dcases_mov)),
    d2cases_mov_4 = c(NA,diff(dcases_mov)),
    leaving_mov = movavg(percent_leaving_home, 7, type = "s"),
    # dleaving_mov = movavg(dleaving, 7),
    # d2leaving_mov = movavg(d2leaving, 7),
    dleaving_mov = c(NA,diff(leaving_mov)),
    d2leaving_mov = c(NA,diff(dleaving_mov)),
    leaving4 = c(rep(NA,4), scc_cases_sd_daily$percent_leaving_home[1:(nrow(bay_sd_daily)-4)]),
    dleaving4 = c(NA,diff(leaving4)),
    d2leaving4 = c(NA,NA,diff(leaving4, differences = 2)),
    leaving3 = c(rep(NA,3), scc_cases_sd_daily$percent_leaving_home[1:(nrow(bay_sd_daily)-3)]),
    leaving3_mov = movavg(leaving3, 7, type = "s"),
    dleaving3_mov = c(NA,diff(leaving3_mov)),
    d2leaving3_mov = c(NA,NA,diff(leaving3_mov, differences = 2)),
    leaving5 = c(rep(NA,5), scc_cases_sd_daily$percent_leaving_home[1:(nrow(bay_sd_daily)-5)]),
    leaving5_mov = movavg(leaving5, 7, type = "s"),
    dleaving5_mov = c(NA,diff(leaving5_mov)),
    d2leaving5_mov = c(NA,NA,diff(leaving5_mov, differences = 2)),
    leaving6dif = c(rep(NA,6), scc_cases_sd_daily$leaving_home_dif[1:(nrow(bay_sd_daily)-6)]), 
    leaving6dif_mov = movavg(leaving6dif, 7, type = "s"),
    past_cases = c(NA, scc_cases_sd_daily$total_cases_by_day[1:(nrow(bay_sd_daily)-1)]), 
    cases_growth_daily = (dcases / past_cases)*100,
    cases_growth_daily_mov = movavg(cases_growth_daily, 7, type = "s")
  ) %>% 
  filter(date >= "2020-03-01")

# get the SMC data on cases and social distancing
smc_blockgroups <- readRDS("/Users/simonespeizer/Documents/2020 Spring Quarter/CEE 218Z/covid19/smc_blockgroups.rds")

smc_cases_sd_daily <- bay_sd %>% 
  filter(date >= min(bay_county_cases_daily$date)) %>%
  filter(origin_census_block_group %in% smc_blockgroups$origin_census_block_group) %>%
  group_by(date) %>%
  summarize(total_at_home = sum(completely_home_device_count), total_devices = sum(device_count)) %>%
  mutate(
    percent_at_home = total_at_home*100/total_devices, 
    percent_leaving_home = (100 - percent_at_home)
  ) %>% 
  left_join(
    bay_county_cases %>%
    filter(county == "San Mateo") %>% 
    group_by(date) %>%
    summarize(total_cases_by_day = sum(confirmed_cases)) 
  ) %>% 
  mutate(
    log_cases = log(total_cases_by_day)
  )

# get the baseline percent of people at home
pre_case_growth_at_home <- bay_sd %>%
  filter(date < min(bay_county_cases_daily$date)) %>%
  filter(origin_census_block_group %in% smc_blockgroups$origin_census_block_group) %>%
  summarize(total_at_home = sum(completely_home_device_count), total_devices = sum(device_count)) %>%
  mutate(percent_at_home = total_at_home*100/total_devices, percent_leaving_home = (100 - percent_at_home))

# obtain difference in percent of people at home
smc_cases_sd_daily <- smc_cases_sd_daily %>%
  mutate(leaving_home_dif = percent_leaving_home - pre_case_growth_at_home$percent_leaving_home[1])
